The article discusses the confirmation of Gina Haspel as the new Director of the Central Intelligence Agency (CIA) by the Senate. Haspel, who previously served as the Deputy Director of the CIA, has a long history of public service and has received numerous awards for her work. She is the first woman in the CIA's history to climb the ranks to become Deputy Director and the first woman to be nominated for CIA Director. Haspel is highly regarded for her objective and unbiased assessments, as well as her commitment to the rule of law and Congressional oversight. Many national security experts, including former Secretaries of State and former CIA Director Leon Panetta, have expressed support for her nomination. The article concludes by emphasizing the importance of confirming Haspel swiftly, highlighting her sense of patriotism and dedication to protecting the country.